element_texts.text:
O in thy peaceful path of life, may no rude thorns be found, no sorrow, anguish, care or strife. Thy bosom's peace to wound. 
But may some sound celestial guide invisible to thee by day and night every side Thy constant guardian be. 
The roll conduct thy wandering feet when the worlds winter lowers where bloom perennial flowers. 
And when he leaves his charge at last, and thou to earth art given, then may thy spirit that we love, Hours safely to them climbs above, and find its home in heaven.

To our parents 
1. Father! Mother! do not leave us, go no more from home away; o! if you do you sure will grieve us, we will be good if you will stay.
2. When we so love to live together, why will you scatter us all around, grandmother, sister, little brother, we're all in different placed found. 
3. Tis time our friends all kindly treat us when were committed to their core; with smiles and words of love they great us, and listen to our simple prayer. 
4. But "home sweet home" to us is clearer, a mother's smile, a mother's kiss, and when we're fondly gathered near her, O! no where else is joy like this. 
Father! Mother! Do not leave us, your long, long journeys how we dread. So rush up home, O! how you grieve us, It seems as this you both were dead.
